our memory in mind when developing apps therefore leaving your android device mercilessly trying to run these inefficiently built programs. Its time you take charge!</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">2. <a href=\"http://www.appstorehq.com/startupauditor-android-174324/app\" target=\"_blank\">Startup Auditor</a></span>\r\n-  Another huge memory and processor hog with any computer system whether a mobile phone or computer alike is the startup processes. This application allows you to kill any start up process. However, I highly recommend spending the $.99 and get the full version to automatically kill any process on start up and keep it killed if it tries to relaunch (as many applications that are developed today do).</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">3. <a href=\"http://www.androidfreeware.net/download-timeriffic.html\" target=\"_blank\">Timeriffic</a></span> -  Another huge component to conserving battery on your Android Incredible phone is screen brightness, ringing volume, and more. With this app you choose at what time and what days you would like certain brightness levels and ringing volumes to increase or decrease. This not only saves you time in the long run from having to manually change all of these options, but it also is more accurate then having to slide a slider that is highly interactive.</p>','Best Apps to Save Battery for Android!','','publish','open','open','','best-apps-to-save-battery-for-android','','','2010-09-15 21:56:38','2010-09-15 21:56:38','',0,'http://www.josephdickinson.com/?p=228',0,'post','',3),(229,1,'2010-08-22 23:44:39','2010-08-22 23:44:39','<p><div class=\"str\"> 1. Open source Development</div> - </p>\n','5 Best Features of Droid Incredible','','inherit','open','open','','228-revision','','','2010-08-22 23:44:39','2010-08-22 23:44:39','',228,'http://www.josephdickinson.com/228-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(9,1,'2010-08-04 11:30:45','2010-08-04 11:30:45','<p><span class=\"str\">Greetings!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>On my blog, I will be writing 