tely unsatisfied customers who decide to outsource their web development and in the end waste their own time and money and have nothing to show for it. Don\'t be that person; heed my advice.</p>','3 Critical Problems for Internet Startups','','publish','open','open','','3-must-needed-considerations-for-internet-start-ups','','\nhttp://www.josephdickinson.com/top-four-reasons-offshoring-is-bad-for-startups/','2010-09-15 21:16:56','2010-09-15 21:16:56','',0,'http://www.josephdickinson.com/?p=232',0,'post','',0),(230,1,'2010-09-14 01:22:46','2010-09-14 01:22:46','<div class=\"str\">1. <a href=\"http://www.androlib.com/android.application.com-rechild-advancedtaskkiller-jCEw.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Task Killer</a></div>\n-  Have you ever entered task manager in Windows to kill awfully programmed programs? Its about time you download this application now, kill virtually any app on your android device.  Many developers aren\'t keeping your processor or your memory in mind when developing apps therefore leaving your android device mercilessly trying to run these inefficiently built programs. Its time you take charge!\n<div class=\"str\">2. <a href=\"http://www.appstorehq.com/startupauditor-android-174324/app\" target=\"_blank\">Startup Auditor</a></div>\n-  Another huge memory and processor hog with any computer system whether a mobile phone or computer alike is the startup processes. This application allows you to kill any start up process. However, I highly recommend spending the $.99 and get the full version to automatically kill any process on start up and keep it killed if it tries to relaunch (as many applications that are developed today do).\n<div class=\"str\">3. <a href=\"http://www.androidfreeware.net/download-timeriffic.html\" target=\"_blank\">Timeriffic</a></div> -  Another huge component to conserving battery on your Android Incredible phone is screen brightness, ringing volume, and more. With this app you choose at what time and what days you would like certain brightness levels and ringing volumes to increase or decrease. This not only saves you time in the long run from having to manually change all of these options, but it also is more accurate then having to slide a slider that is highly interactive. ','Best Apps to Save Battery for Android!','','inherit','open','open','','228-revision-2','','','2010-09-14 01:22:46','2010-09-14 01:22:46','',228,'http://www.josephdickinson.com/228-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(96,1,'2010-08-05 18:15:33','2010-08-05 18:15:33','<h2>What is net neutrality?</h2>\r\n<p>You can think of the term \"net neutrality\" as organization who protects the common individual from the government being able to control everything we do on the internet from shopping to selling to well... everything online.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>By the net being \'neutral\', this helps protect us from governments being able to enforce harsh restrictions on the content, websites, and platforms we utilize. While, the internet was first used as a way for communication in armed services, it does not mean that they can control the portal that billions of people nationwide utilize everything from banking, shopping, marketing, and much much more.</p>\r\n<h2>How does it affect you?</h2>\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">Life without online banking</span> - Can you imagine it? Everything would have to revert to the old method: banks would need to hire new tellers, people would need to spend a lot of time in the branches, atm machines would be flooded with annoyed customers who just want that get their hands on that $100 to go down the shore this weekend, and individuals lifestyles would just be astray</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">Decreased video streaming</span> - Imagine if the government created a law that tracks your ip address and only allows each ip address to watch say, five hours per video a month online? The millions upon millions of users who use Youtube and other popular video sharing websites would be heartbroken.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">Designated website viewing</span> - This is probably the worst thought of all of them, imagine net neutrality isn\'t put into effect and you can only see certain websites? Imagine if the only website\'s you could view were few and far between? Do you realize that this could happen very soon if net neutrality isn\'t enacted?</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>Just think of the amazing jobs the internet has produced for people, how it drastically has changed the way people communicate, and what disaster it could cause to Information Technology if we do not fight to enact this into legislation?</p>','Your life without net neutrality','','publish','open','open','','your-life-without-net-neutralty','','','2010-09-15 20:18:01','2010-09-15 20:18:01','',0,'http://www.josephdickinson.com/?p=96',0,'post','',0),(235,1,'2010-09-15 19:54:47','2010-09-15 19:54:47','<div class=\"str\">1. Outsourcing</div> - <p>First, but not least, are you going to outsource or are you not? The real question you need to ponder is making a bit more <a href=\"http://www.josephdickinson.com/top-four-reasons-offshoring-is-bad-for-startups/\">profit now</a> and not getting the best quality of work worth it or is building up a solid customer base over time more important to you?</p>\r\n<div class=\"str\">2. Saturated market : not your problem</div> - <p>Have you established how you will be one step ahead of your competition? Let\'s take for example: Web Development firms - there are a million and one web development firms out there, but you still see many new ventures starting up everyday. The reason is - they have that spark or unique way of developing websites that sets them apart.</p>\r\n<div class=\"str\">3. Location, Location, Location</div> - <p>No, not physical location! Location on Google. Far too many internet start ups think they have created their masterpiece of a website they envisioned and now everyone and their grandma will be flocking to visit it; think again! Even with the most basic s