ware when you first get it out of the box! Apple has done that for you, Apple preinstalls on its macbooks everything from Python to Php to AppleScript to C all editable in the native program X-Code (similiar to Visual Studio) - programmers : program from the get go!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When all is said and done, the TCO for own a mac when you factor in time, money, and learning easily outbeats any PC-competitor. It runs like a champ out of the box. I\'ve owned both 3 different PC brands, 1 macbook, and 1 macbook pro. I cannot emphasive it enough; a mac comes out on top either way</p>','How a Macbook Will Knock Your Socks Off','','inherit','open','open','','209-revision-5','','','2010-08-14 00:05:55','2010-08-14 00:05:55','',209,'http://www.josephdickinson.com/209-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(216,1,'2010-08-14 00:06:23','2010-08-14 00:06:23','<p>When looking to buy a computer the first thing you might see is a cheap dell for $500 and jump at it! But, you should reconsider, while a macbook can be a whopping $1000+ in the long run, the TCO (total cost of ownership) will be a lot less. I\'ll show you how:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">1. Virtually no viruses</span> - While the mac operating system, may have a handful of viruses - the fact of the matter is : most people (to date) do not need antivirus. How does this save you? Well, consider you run a business and use your laptop to store information about clients and all of a sudden a virus steals all of the confidential customer data and sends them all hate mail while at the same thing steals all of the social security numbers and open accounts in them. Lesson learned: mac users typically would not have to worry about this.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">2. Much faster</span> - The operating system behind a macbook is built behind the legendary: unix operating system. This increases not just your everyday browsing capabilities, but let\'s you develop software quicker, simultaneously run multiple applications, and o