 is screen brightness, ringing volume, and more. With this app you choose at what time and what days you would like certain brightness levels and ringing volumes to increase or decrease. This not only saves you time in the long run from having to manually change all of these options, but it also is more accurate then having to slide a slider that is highly interactive. ','Best Apps to Save Battery for Android!','','inherit','open','open','','228-revision-3','','','2010-09-14 01:28:11','2010-09-14 01:28:11','',228,'http://www.josephdickinson.com/228-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(241,1,'2010-08-14 02:16:55','2010-08-14 02:16:55','<p>When looking to buy a computer the first thing you might see is a cheap dell for $500 and jump at it! But, you should reconsider, while a macbook can be a whopping $1000+ in the long run, the TCO (total cost of ownership) will be a lot less. I\'ll show you how:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">1. Virtually no viruses</span> - While the mac operating system, may have a handful of viruses - the fact of the matter is : most people (to date) do not need antivirus. How does this save you? Well, consider you run a business and use your laptop to store information about clients and all of a sudden a virus steals all of the confidential customer data and sends them all hate mail while at the same thing steals all of the social security numbers and open accounts in them. Lesson learned: mac users typically would not have to worry about this.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">2. Much faster</span> - The operating system behind a macbook is built behind the legendary: unix operating system. This increases not just your everyday browsing capabilities, but let\'s you develop software quicker, simultaneously run multiple applications, and on the off chance you need to leave your mac for the day; it will within seconds come and warmly welcome you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">3. Native Backup Built In</span> - Time Machine! Every time you make an edit to something on your harddrive, Time Machine backs up that file immediately to an external drive (such as an External Hard drive, Flash Drive, etc). The best part of it is, if you want to backup to an earlier date, even years ago, you can with two clicks! Can you say no more losing your data?</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">4. Easier Program Install / Uninstall</span> - Simply drag and drop a program into the /applications/ directory on your mac and voila! You have installed a program. If you choose to then delete that file all you need to do is right click and \"Move to Trash\"; file deleted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">5. Longer Battery Life</span> - Have you ever been sitting in starbucks (or a local coffee shop) without your power cable and after 2 hours your computer is ready to die? Worry to longer, a macbook has 4-5 hours of battery life whether its idling or working between multiple programs; kiss good-bye those days where you need to furious save your work because your battery is going to die.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">6. Need Windows? No Problem</span> - Have you thought about a windows program that you just can\'t get your hands off of? Well, you\'re in luck, by using Cross Over or Parallels or Mac\'s Native solution Boot Camp - you can natively run windows just like if you have a clunker PC to work on rejoice, you have the best of both worlds!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">7. Develop out of the box</span> - No need to install all of this software when you first get it out of the box! Apple has done that for you, Apple preinstalls on its macbooks everything from Python to Php to AppleScript to C all editable in the native program X-Code (similiar to Visual Studio) - programmers : program from the get go!</p>\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<p>When all is said and done, the TCO for own a mac when you factor in time, money, and learning easily outbeats any PC-competitor. It runs like a champ out of the box. I\'ve owned both 3 different PC brands, 1 macbook, and 1 macbook pro. I cannot emphasive it enough; a mac comes out on top either way</p>','How a Macbook Will Knock Your Socks Off','','inherit','open','open','','209-revision-8','','','2010-08-14 02:16:55','2010-08-14 02:16:55','',209,'http://www.josephdickinson.com/209-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(242,1,'2010-08-13 12:10:38','2010-08-13 12:10:38','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"/wp-content/images/nbooks.png\" alt=\"Why To Buy Netbook\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many people think net-books are just not powerful enough for their demands. But, you maybe be enticed by their price-to-performance ratio. This especially should be your computer if you all do you is instant messaging, internet browsing, and other light-cpu tasks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">1. Initial Cost</span> - Are you in the market for a new computer? How does $200 to $300 sound? This does not sacrifice what you can do however, you can just as easily connect to your facebook, or twitter, or stream Youtube videos.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">2. Option not with Windows</span> - For those of you (myself included) who absolutely loath Microsoft - you can now rejoice: some net books are offered with Windows 7 or a distribution of linux. In fact, most net books today can run both simultaneously (if you\'re that geeky).</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">3. Easier Portability</span> - Did you know - some net books weight 1-2 lbs? This is a significant difference both when putting your net book in your laptop and when your carrying it around. Other primarily windows-based net books can weigh anywhere from 5 to 8 lbs.</p>\r\n\r\n','Three Reasons To Buy A Netbook','','inherit','open','open','','202-revision-6','','','2010-08-13 12:10:38','2010-08-13 12:10:38','',202,'http://www.josephdickinson.com/202-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(243,1,'2010-08-08 02:19:49','2010-08-08 02:19:49','Whether or not you are a current smart phone owner, have you briefly looked at your past cell phone bill? Most cell phone plans nowadays can be as much as $100 per month for one phone, never mind a smart phone.\r\n\r\n<center><img title=\"Smart Phones\" src=\"http://www.crunchgear.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/07/blackberry_iphone.jpg\" alt=\"Smart phone devices Iphone Blackberry\" width=\"168\" height=\"126\" /></center>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"str\">Give up the smart phone</span> - Have you realized that there are an emerging amount of android-based cell phones like the Motorola Droid, Droid Incredible, iPhone, etc out there? Their reeling you in by acting like its a cheap investment by only having to spend $50 for upfront, but what their really aimed at targeting is the bill at the end of the month with a data plan. Let\'s analyze how much a plan can really cost you:\r\n<div style=\"float: left; width: 275px;\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"openbull\">$50-$60/mo (minutes)</li>\r\n	<li class=\"openbull\">$10-$20/mo (texting)</li>\r\n	<li class=\"openbull\">$15-$30 (data plan)</li>\r\n	<li class=\"openbull\" style=\"color: #599b21;\">Total: $75 - $110</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"float: right; width: 275px;\">\r\n<em>Verizon:</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"openbull\">$60-$70/mo (minutes)</li>\r\n	<li class=\"openbull\">$5-$25/mo (texting)</li>\r\n	<li class=\"openbull\">$20-$30 (data plan)</li>\r\n	<li class=\"openbull\" style=\"color: #599b21;\">Total: $85 - $125</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">Lose Unlimited Texting</span> - For the average 30 to 50 year old they are not sending out a mere 1000+ texts per month. They may send out the occasional text to their spouse or sister. Unlimited texting is only cost-beneficial if you are sending out 1000s of texts per week like many young teens do everything. Saving that extra $10+ per month really adds up.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">Save on Un-needed Minutes</span> - Have you given your minute usage a gander lately? Many people easily are giving themselves the short end of the stick, they buy hundreds and hundreds of minutes and hardly use the majority of them. You really should give everyone a limit who is on the plan (obviously the plan owner with the most) and stick to it. This way, you maximize the money in your pocket and your usage. So, this was, you win; not the cell phone company.<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When all is said and done, you ultimately choose what you want and what you need on your cell phone plan. However, by utilizing these three simple steps when choosing and/or modifying your cell phone bill you can pocket these extra hundred dollars per year instead of giving it away.</p>','Save over $100 per year on cell phones','','inherit','open','open','','122-revision-44','','','2010-08-08 02:19:49','2010-08-08 02:19:49','',122,'http://www.josephdickinson.com/122-revision-44/',0,'revision','',0),(244,1,'2010-08-05 20:17:55','2010-08-05 20:17:55','<h2>The top 4:</h2>\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">1. Loss of Business Focus</span> - Current employees who are onsite are not going to be too convinced that you, as the Ceo, are making decisions that are best for everyone\'s future in the company. Many of these employees are the ones you started the business with and now your stabbing them in the back. You still want these back-stabbed employees to still bring the level of dedication that they brought fresh into the company? Kiss that good bye.<br></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">2. Abandoned relationships</span> - Now that you - the ceo have decided to save money and get piss-pour work overseas you may not realize it, but in the process are destroying colleague relationships that have been established decades ago and by laying off others, I am certain you will not make current employees happy.<br></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">3. Time Zone Differences</span> - Imagine you run a small business ( > 10 employees ) you decide to save some more money for yourself (as if you don\'t do that already). Meanwhile, your new employee overseas is running into a