 behind a macbook is built behind the legendary: unix operating system. This increases not just your everyday browsing capabilities, but let\'s you develop software quicker, simultaneously run multiple applications, and on the off chance you need to leave your mac for the day; it will within seconds come and warmly welcome you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">3. Native Backup Built In</span> - Time Machine! Every time you make an edit to something on your harddrive, Time Machine backs up that file immediately to an external drive (such as an External Hard drive, Flash Drive, etc). The best part of it is, if you want to backup to an earlier date, even years ago, you can with two clicks! Can you say no more losing your data?</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">4. Easier Program Install / Uninstall</span> - Simply drag and drop a program into the /applications/ directory on your mac and voila! You have installed a program. If you choose to then delete that file all you need to do is right click and \"Move to Trash\"; file deleted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">5. Longer Battery Life</span> - Have you ever been sitting in starbucks (or a local coffee shop) without your power cable and after 2 hours your computer is ready to die? Worry to longer, a macbook has 4-5 hours of battery life whether its idling or working between multiple programs; kiss good-bye those days where you need to furious save your work because your battery is going to die.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">6. Need Windows? No Problem</span> - Have you thought about a windows program that you just can\'t get your hands off of? Well, you\'re in luck, by using Cross Over or Parallels or Mac\'s Native solution Boot Camp - you can natively run windows just like if you have a clunker PC to work on rejoice, you have the best of both worlds!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"str\">7. Develop out of the box</span> - No need to install all of this software when you first get it out of the box! Apple has done that for you, Apple preinstalls on its macbooks everything from Python to Php to AppleScript to C all editable in the native program X-Code (similiar to Visual Studio) - programmers : program from the get go!</p>\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<p>When all is said and done, the TCO for own a mac when you factor in time, money, and learning easily outbeats any PC-competitor. It runs like a champ out of the box. I\'ve owned both 3 different PC brands, 1 macbook, and 1 macbook pro. I cannot emphasive it enough; a mac comes out on top either way</p>','How a Macbook Will Knock Your Socks Off','','inherit','open','open','','209-revision-10','','','2010-09-15 20:17:57','2010-09-15 20:17:57','',209,'http://www.josephdickinson.com/209-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(273,1,'2010-08-14 02:44:34','2010-08-14 02:44:34','<p>Below shows some of my web development work as a consultant working for varying-sized businesses through the Philadelphia-South Jersey-Delaware area.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<h2>FutureProofPC</h2>\r\n<p style=\"width:293px; float:left; padding-right:5px; margin-bottom:10px;\">FutureProofPC came to me with the vision of creating a cutting-edge homepage that represented its computer repair clients needs.<br> I created a site and implemented a ticket-support system that added functionality for their customers problems to be reported instantly instead of via email.<br><span class=\"str\">Languages: </span> xHtml, Css, Php, mySql </p>\r\n<p width:275px; float:right; border:#000;\"><img src=\"/wp-content/images/c_fppc.png\" width=\"275\" height=\"109\" alt=\"FutureProofPC\" /></p>\r\n<div class=\"clear\"> </div>\r\n\r\n<h2>K and A Carosella</h2>\r\n<p style=\"width:293px; float:left; padding-right:5px; margin-bottom:10px;\">KandA Carosella were embarassed by how their image on the web was so \"1990s\". I ended up creating a web 2.0 design that much better represented their quality of work and business. <br><span class=\"str\">Languages: </span> xHtml, Css, jQuery, Php, mySql</p>\r\n<p wid