rst ever<a title=\"html5\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML5\" target=\"_blank\">HTML5</a> website and first ever completely hand-coded wordpress template.\r\n<h3>A few thoughts about html5:</h3>\r\n<strong>1. </strong><strong>Love the doctype declaration!</strong> - <code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</code>\r\n\r\nNow instead of having to specify a doctype such as xhtml transitional dtd or strict dtd (my old fav!), you just call that one identifier. Now if only IE9 will fully support it!\r\n\r\n<strong>2. The support for -moz-border-radius </strong>this is by far the most useful component of html5 I\'ve personally dealt with so far. Instead of having to create nice, gorgeous round edges for webpages you can easily specify in literally less than 4 lines of css code all edges of a given &lt;div&gt;. Other benefits include decreasing page size, page load time, and utimately save you a ton of hours in a distro of photoshop! Get to it!\r\n\r\n<strong>3. And finally, shadows and animation </strong>something I had heavily considered adding to this new version of the site, however due to one lousy browser, IE, which has god awful support for anything \'hip\' nowadays on the world-wide-web :) I decided to leave it out for this version only. <a title=\"Html5 Examples\" href=\"http://pushingpixels.at/experiments/dynamic_shadow/\" target=\"_blank\">PushingPixels</a>, however, has quite a number of interesting tutorials.\r\n\r\nPretty soon I will create a list of improvements I have for this site, so stick close by !\r\n\r\nOh yeah... and comments on the new version are always welcome!','The New HTML5-ified Homepage','','publish','open','open','','the-new-html5-ified-homepage','','','2011-01-05 03:12:53','2011-01-05 03:12:53','',0,'http://www.josephdickinson.com/?p=322',0,'post','',0),(323,1,'2011-01-05 02:57:47','2011-01-05 02:57:47','Just thought I\'d update everyone on the new homepage layout. It actually was my first ever <a title=\"html5\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/w